WEBVTT

00:01.160 --> 00:02.628
- Previously... on Being Human.

00:02.670 --> 00:04.661
- I may be a flesh eater.
- Like a zombie?

00:04.700 --> 00:06.794
- Stay away from Sally.

00:06.840 --> 00:09.309
She doesn't think she will,
but she'll kill you.

00:09.340 --> 00:11.160
- Stevie, wait!

00:11.210 --> 00:14.430
- Ghost doors can't be the same.
- Something is very wrong.

00:14.480 --> 00:16.175
Everyone's door
is their door.

00:16.210 --> 00:18.144
- We have to figure out
what's on the other side of it.

00:18.180 --> 00:20.319
- But you're all in trouble
with me around.

00:26.690 --> 00:28.385
- (Kat):
My ex is here.

00:28.420 --> 00:30.559
- I'm Aidan Waite.
- Oh, right! Sorry.

00:30.590 --> 00:32.524
Nice to meet you.
Jeff Weston.

00:34.430 --> 00:35.659
- This is Pete.

00:35.700 --> 00:37.395
- Oh! Hi there!

00:38.930 --> 00:40.864
- Oh my God!

00:40.900 --> 00:42.709
- Josh... Josh, go!

00:44.040 --> 00:45.906
- Give me their names.

00:45.940 --> 00:48.602
- I wasn't exactly paying
attention to names, OK?

00:48.640 --> 00:50.176
I was trying to save Pete.

00:50.210 --> 00:52.178
- They killed Pete.
That shouldn't have happened.

00:52.220 --> 00:54.609
- Yeah, because you
never should have told them

00:54.650 --> 00:56.618
that drinking wolf blood
inoculates them.

00:56.650 --> 00:58.948
- The truth was gonna get out.
I got ahead of it.

00:58.990 --> 01:01.960
I put the word out that you
and Nora were off-limits.

01:01.990 --> 01:04.754
I should have remembered Pete.
He didn't deserve that.

01:04.790 --> 01:06.098
- No.

01:06.130 --> 01:07.950
- I told Blake it
only takes a sip.

01:08.000 --> 01:09.593
- Yeah, that's a real shocker

01:09.630 --> 01:12.190
that she and her buddies
didn't use a little restraint.

01:13.400 --> 01:14.868
Listen, I understand

01:14.900 --> 01:17.301
that you were trying
to protect Nora and me.

01:17.340 --> 01:21.470
I just... I can't believe
that you would side with them

01:21.510 --> 01:23.376
over someone like Pete.

01:23.410 --> 01:25.640
- I didn't pick sides!
- Yes, you did!

01:26.920 --> 01:30.515
And the scariest thing is
you don't even realize it.

01:33.920 --> 01:35.684
I'll see you later.

01:38.060 --> 01:40.051
(Siren wailing)

01:44.100 --> 01:45.226
- Morning, Kenny.

01:46.940 --> 01:48.430
Something wrong?

01:48.470 --> 01:50.768
- They found a match for
my bone-marrow transplant.

01:51.810 --> 01:54.131
- That's great!
When can they do it?

01:54.180 --> 01:56.069
- They could schedule it
for never.

01:56.110 --> 01:58.272
I'm not gonna be there.
I'm leaving.

01:58.310 --> 02:00.950
- What are you...
OK, slow down.

02:00.980 --> 02:02.482
With your immune system,

02:02.520 --> 02:04.579
there's a hundred people
between here and Admitting

02:04.620 --> 02:07.453
who'd kill you just by breathing
in your general direction.

02:09.930 --> 02:11.329
- Then turn me.

02:14.300 --> 02:16.428
I knew it.
You're backing out again.

02:16.470 --> 02:17.562
- No!

02:17.600 --> 02:18.920
- You were never
gonna do it.

02:18.970 --> 02:20.938
- The deal was
when you turned 18,

02:20.970 --> 02:22.506
if nothing better came along.

02:22.540 --> 02:23.666
This is better.

02:25.340 --> 02:27.274
Do the procedure.

02:27.310 --> 02:29.244
If it doesn't work,
then I'll turn you.

02:29.280 --> 02:31.977
- I'm not spending months
getting pumped full of chemo,

02:32.010 --> 02:35.344
puking, losing my hair,

02:35.380 --> 02:38.281
crossing my fingers that
my lungs don't shut down

02:38.320 --> 02:40.186
before I even get
the transplant.

02:40.220 --> 02:42.621
And for what?
A 25% success rate?

02:42.660 --> 02:45.789
- Kenny, you've been waiting
for years for this donor.

02:45.830 --> 02:48.424
And if you say no,
then by tomorrow morning,

02:48.460 --> 02:50.792
they'll move to the
next name on the list

02:50.830 --> 02:52.992
and your one shot is gone.

02:53.040 --> 02:57.159
Do this and you can
have a life, a real life.

02:57.210 --> 02:59.372
- For how long?
A couple of years maybe?

02:59.410 --> 03:01.970
That's if my body doesn't
reject the transplant.

03:02.010 --> 03:04.149
I go through all of this

03:04.180 --> 03:07.639
and the thing that ends up
killing me is me.

03:07.680 --> 03:09.387
(Chuckles)

03:11.190 --> 03:13.386
So, all great options.

03:17.490 --> 03:20.528
- If you leave, you're never
gonna see your parents again.

03:20.560 --> 03:23.325
Think about what
that would do to them.

03:23.370 --> 03:25.498
- Give them
their lives back.

03:25.530 --> 03:27.567
Oh, come on,
think about it.

03:27.600 --> 03:30.001
They have felt so guilty
that I'm in here,

03:30.040 --> 03:32.839
they have completely
forgotten about themselves.

03:32.880 --> 03:35.178
They've spent their
life savings and then some

03:35.210 --> 03:36.405
on surgeries like this.

03:36.450 --> 03:38.248
They deserve a life too,

03:38.280 --> 03:42.069
and one that they don't
spend in a sickroom.

03:42.120 --> 03:44.680
- You'll be dead
in 2 days out there.

03:44.720 --> 03:46.085
- Not if I'm what you are.

03:46.120 --> 03:47.986
- I'm not gonna let you leave.
- OK then.

03:48.020 --> 03:49.522
- I'm not gonna
let you leave!

03:49.560 --> 03:50.857
- It's fine.

03:51.930 --> 03:54.399
I can wait, you know,
until your shift's over

03:54.430 --> 03:55.989
and I'll sneak out.

03:56.030 --> 03:57.668
I'll call Blake.

03:57.700 --> 04:01.933
You know, maybe join some
vampire meet-up or something.

04:01.970 --> 04:05.406
OK, regardless of
your help or not...

04:06.780 --> 04:09.078
I'm leaving today, OK?

04:09.110 --> 04:12.319
So... what's it gonna be?

04:23.090 --> 04:25.127
(Air hissing)

04:25.160 --> 04:26.753
(Sighs)

04:37.270 --> 04:38.533
- OK, great.

04:38.570 --> 04:40.208
We don't have a lot
of time. Come on.

04:40.240 --> 04:43.744
* Take it off
Take it in *

04:43.780 --> 04:47.239
* Take off all the thoughts
of what we've been *

04:47.280 --> 04:50.580
* Take a look hesitate

04:50.620 --> 04:54.158
* Take a picture
you could never recreate *

04:54.190 --> 04:56.830
* Write a song
Make a note... *

04:56.860 --> 04:58.624
(Laughing)

04:58.660 --> 05:01.652
* For the lump that sits
inside your throat *

05:01.700 --> 05:04.965
* Change the locks
Change the scene... *

05:05.000 --> 05:07.332
(Kenny laughing)

05:07.370 --> 05:09.702
- It's so disgusting.
I love it!

05:12.140 --> 05:13.630
Are you seeing this?

05:13.680 --> 05:15.933
This grass, it is so...
It's so green!

05:15.980 --> 05:17.141
- OK, all right.

05:17.180 --> 05:19.148
Maybe take it down a notch

05:19.180 --> 05:21.547
before you're arrested
for shrooming in public.

05:21.580 --> 05:23.139
- Oh yeah, sorry.
- Come on.

05:23.190 --> 05:24.339
- Thank you. Sorry.

05:24.390 --> 05:25.619
- You think this is intense,

05:25.650 --> 05:27.789
wait till after
you're turned.

05:27.820 --> 05:29.549
- Well, um,

05:29.590 --> 05:33.299
I know that I pressured you
to turn me into what you are,

05:33.330 --> 05:37.824
but can I have one day
as a teenager, please?

05:37.870 --> 05:40.498
- You're about to spend
an eternity as a teenager.

05:40.540 --> 05:43.464
- Well, yeah, but not as,
like, a human one.

05:43.510 --> 05:45.638
I've never gotten
to do that.

05:45.670 --> 05:48.002
I wanna drink
and eat and do drugs.

05:48.040 --> 05:49.849
- OK, slow down, Scarface.

05:49.880 --> 05:53.339
- I just wanna do all the stuff
that won't affect me

05:53.380 --> 05:56.145
when I'm a, you know...

05:56.180 --> 05:57.739
lord of the night.

05:57.790 --> 05:59.383
(Sighs)

06:00.460 --> 06:04.090
- One day. And don't
ever call us that.

06:04.130 --> 06:05.529
- Sorry.

06:05.560 --> 06:08.097
- When we get
to my place...

06:08.130 --> 06:12.533
* Your Trojan's in my head

06:16.240 --> 06:19.870
* Take it off
Take it in *

06:19.910 --> 06:24.746
* Take off all the thoughts
of what we've been **

06:27.880 --> 06:29.848
- Whatever Donna has planned
for my soul when I die,

06:29.890 --> 06:30.846
that's bad enough.

06:30.890 --> 06:34.383
But if I hurt you guys?
I can't deal with that.

06:34.420 --> 06:36.889
- I'm not padlocking you
into your own room.

06:36.930 --> 06:38.250
- Josh, you have to!

06:38.290 --> 06:39.758
- I'm not going to do that!

06:39.800 --> 06:40.824
- You have to, Josh.

06:40.860 --> 06:43.568
I'm starving and may not
be able to control myself.

06:43.600 --> 06:46.433
You guys need to walk down
the aisle intact.

06:48.500 --> 06:51.902
I wanted to be at
your wedding, you know.

06:51.940 --> 06:53.430
I know this sounds cheesy,

06:53.480 --> 06:55.733
but you guys are seriously
the hope for the future.

06:57.610 --> 06:59.715
I wanted to make a toast.

06:59.750 --> 07:00.876
I wanted to cry

07:00.920 --> 07:03.548
and I wanted to
get drunk and dance

07:03.590 --> 07:06.389
and say inappropriate things.

07:06.420 --> 07:08.081
I love you guys.

07:09.930 --> 07:11.557
So, please just...

07:12.630 --> 07:14.428
Please lock me up.

07:14.460 --> 07:16.724
And use 2 locks.

07:16.770 --> 07:19.068
I may have zombie strength
and not know it.

07:19.100 --> 07:22.559
- We're not giving up on you.
And we are gonna find you food.

07:22.610 --> 07:23.736
- You are food.

07:25.640 --> 07:27.074
- OK...

07:32.780 --> 07:36.011
<i>Let's get moving.
The meet and greets...</i>

07:40.960 --> 07:43.588
Hey, guys.
You remember Kenny, right?

07:43.630 --> 07:45.485
- Sure, yeah,
from the hospital.

07:45.530 --> 07:47.953
- Where he's usually sealed
in a protective room

07:48.000 --> 07:49.593
that prevents him
from dying.

07:49.630 --> 07:52.600
From what I understand.
Hi, Kenny.

07:52.640 --> 07:54.438
- You haven't
told them yet?

07:54.470 --> 07:55.631
- No, he hasn't told us.

07:55.670 --> 07:57.263
- Why don't you
throw your stuff

07:57.310 --> 07:59.608
downstairs in the basement
in my room,

07:59.640 --> 08:02.337
- Wait, you don't want me to
call you a lord of the night,

08:02.380 --> 08:04.007
but you live in the basement?

08:04.050 --> 08:06.007
- Ha ha, very funny.
Come on.

08:06.050 --> 08:07.449
- I'm just saying.

08:13.790 --> 08:15.485
- So there's that.

08:15.520 --> 08:18.979
- I know this is a surprise,
but Kenny moved up the timeline.

08:19.030 --> 08:20.555
OK...

08:21.560 --> 08:23.824
He gave me clean blood,

08:23.870 --> 08:27.329
so I made a deal to,
uh, save him.

08:27.370 --> 08:30.010
- You mean to turn him?
- Yeah.

08:31.210 --> 08:33.837
- Aidan, how is
cursing him to a life

08:33.880 --> 08:36.850
that you claim to hate
saving him exactly?

08:36.880 --> 08:39.405
- I will keep him in check.

08:39.450 --> 08:43.818
- So he's gonna bunk
with you now, downstairs,

08:43.850 --> 08:45.909
like, for eternity?

08:45.950 --> 08:47.509
- He's going to
stay down there

08:47.560 --> 08:49.187
until he is used
to his new life.

08:49.220 --> 08:50.483
- Between Stevie and Erin,

08:50.530 --> 08:52.999
we don't exactly have
the best track record

08:53.030 --> 08:54.759
with wayward teens, Aidan.

08:54.800 --> 08:56.097
- This will be different.

08:56.130 --> 08:58.360
It has to be different.

08:58.400 --> 09:02.359
I understand you're upset
with me about Pete.

09:02.400 --> 09:05.267
Please do not
punish Kenny for that.

09:05.310 --> 09:06.573
- You're right.

09:08.910 --> 09:11.902
We have so many reasons
to hate what we are.

09:13.920 --> 09:17.049
But if we can use our curse
to help someone,

09:17.090 --> 09:18.717
then I say we do it.

09:22.630 --> 09:24.928
- Did I pretend to put
my stuff away long enough?

09:24.960 --> 09:26.758
- We're good.

09:26.800 --> 09:29.428
- Come on, let's go.

09:34.600 --> 09:36.193
(Door closing)

09:36.240 --> 09:38.902
- I know that you think that
I went too easy on Aidan,

09:38.940 --> 09:41.102
but Kenny's dying.

09:42.850 --> 09:44.944
If that was your friend,

09:44.980 --> 09:47.642
you would do whatever
you could to save them.

09:51.620 --> 09:53.110
- You're right.

09:55.120 --> 09:56.110
Sally!

09:57.960 --> 10:00.054
- I appreciate you guys
trying to protect me,

10:00.100 --> 10:02.398
but going after Donna
is a bad idea.

10:02.430 --> 10:04.159
- What other choice
do we have?

10:04.200 --> 10:06.931
- Donna only gets your soul
if she's alive to collect it.

10:06.970 --> 10:08.665
- Wow, you went dark fast.

10:08.700 --> 10:10.566
- Well, it's either
you or Donna.

10:10.610 --> 10:13.170
When you go through that door,
you're stepping into her world.

10:13.210 --> 10:15.099
So we have to take
her out in our world,

10:15.140 --> 10:17.142
where we have a chance
and we can help you.

10:17.180 --> 10:18.841
- We tried that, remember?

10:18.880 --> 10:21.144
She Vader-choked me and then
I started craving puppies.

10:21.180 --> 10:22.784
I'd rather not
piss her off again,

10:22.820 --> 10:24.242
considering now
she has my soul.

10:24.290 --> 10:26.088
- That time, we wandered in
there like doe-eyed children.

10:26.120 --> 10:29.112
This time, we don't
give her a chance.

10:29.160 --> 10:31.788
- OK, guns and witches.
What could go wrong?

10:31.830 --> 10:33.457
Do you even have a plan?

10:33.500 --> 10:35.059
- Yeah, I'm gonna kill her.

10:37.500 --> 10:40.538
- You sure this is
the right address?

10:40.570 --> 10:42.766
- I'm telling you,

10:42.810 --> 10:45.507
the soup kitchen
was right here.

10:45.540 --> 10:48.805
- A building can't
just disappear.

10:48.840 --> 10:50.376
- Tell that to Donna.

10:52.010 --> 10:53.842
I'm so screwed.

10:56.820 --> 11:00.313
- This is my fault.
I got Sally into this mess.

11:00.360 --> 11:02.010
- She doesn't blame you.

11:03.690 --> 11:06.990
Hey, she got to live,

11:07.030 --> 11:10.796
got her body back,
got a little undertaker action.

11:10.830 --> 11:12.468
- Became a cannibal.

11:12.500 --> 11:14.537
- Let's try not to
focus on the negative.

11:14.570 --> 11:16.390
- There's gotta
be something.

11:16.440 --> 11:19.205
Gotta be something
we can do to help.

11:23.050 --> 11:24.370
(Sighs)

11:24.410 --> 11:26.048
- This won't save anyone,

11:26.080 --> 11:29.448
but it might help take
her mind off what's coming.

11:32.050 --> 11:34.212
What if we got married now?

11:34.260 --> 11:37.082
So that Sally
could be there.

11:40.760 --> 11:43.092
- She's only got,
like, a day or two.

11:43.130 --> 11:44.620
- So we do it fast.

11:45.730 --> 11:48.062
You don't really talk
to your parents anyway.

11:48.100 --> 11:51.138
And the only thing my family
would do is ruin it.

11:52.940 --> 11:55.102
- So just the family
we have here.

11:56.850 --> 11:58.670
- Before we lose it.

12:02.920 --> 12:04.445
Sally?

12:07.290 --> 12:08.917
Sally?

12:15.530 --> 12:17.089
Sally!

12:17.130 --> 12:19.622
- We've gotta find her
before she finds lunch.

12:26.980 --> 12:28.709
- Hey.

12:28.740 --> 12:31.778
- I wasn't sure I was
gonna see you again.

12:31.810 --> 12:34.609
- I wasn't sure if I should
come here, but, um...

12:38.150 --> 12:39.811
I'm running out of options.

12:41.390 --> 12:43.188
And, um...

12:45.160 --> 12:47.629
I feel like I can
tell you everything.

12:47.660 --> 12:50.595
- Except for why your roommates
came home looking like

12:50.630 --> 12:52.394
they were stunt doubles
from a Bourne movie.

12:52.430 --> 12:54.398
- I should've
told you about that.

12:54.440 --> 12:56.829
I will tell you about that.

12:56.870 --> 13:00.033
But right now,
it's just...

13:00.080 --> 13:03.300
My body's, like,
running out of time.

13:06.250 --> 13:07.547
- I'll get my kit.

13:07.580 --> 13:10.220
- I'm actually
past the putty phase.

13:12.520 --> 13:15.410
- What's wrong?
- Um...

13:17.190 --> 13:20.023
The hunger that I was
telling you about...

13:20.060 --> 13:24.668
So when my body started
breaking down, uh...

13:24.700 --> 13:26.668
It's just 'cause...

13:26.700 --> 13:29.362
So regular food
stopped working.

13:29.400 --> 13:31.334
- What's working now?

13:31.370 --> 13:35.500
- Uh, it's more of,
like, a raw-food diet.

13:35.540 --> 13:38.202
- Oh God, you're not talking
about veggies, are you?

13:39.550 --> 13:42.850
- OK, don't freak out.
- I'm not making any promises.

13:42.890 --> 13:44.415
- Human flesh.

13:46.120 --> 13:48.009
Not yours.
I--1... Not yours!

13:48.060 --> 13:51.030
I'm here because I don't
wanna hurt anybody.

13:51.060 --> 13:52.858
Are you kidding?

13:52.900 --> 13:56.200
I would never eat
an actual living...

13:57.430 --> 14:00.695
But, OK, if I don't...
If I don't...

14:00.740 --> 14:04.199
If I don't, then I
at least need to...

14:06.640 --> 14:09.371
OK, I can't believe
I'm saying this.

14:09.410 --> 14:12.209
And I--I don't
expect you to...

14:12.250 --> 14:14.548
I know this is a lot
for you to handle, but...

14:14.580 --> 14:17.049
So, this morning,

14:17.090 --> 14:20.116
I saw this obit
for Mrs. Hanover.

14:20.160 --> 14:21.389
- Sally...

14:21.420 --> 14:22.717
- She didn't have any kids.

14:22.760 --> 14:24.524
She didn't want
a memorial service.

14:24.560 --> 14:25.880
She wanted to be cremated.

14:25.930 --> 14:27.728
- You can't eat Ms. Hanover!

14:27.760 --> 14:30.400
- I know how awful it sounds.
- I don't think you do.

14:30.430 --> 14:31.898
- I do!
I really do, trust me.

14:31.930 --> 14:33.534
You think I wanna be
standing here

14:33.570 --> 14:35.038
in front of the guy I love

14:35.070 --> 14:36.936
asking to eat the dead body
in the freezer?

14:42.510 --> 14:44.478
- I have wanted to tell you

14:44.510 --> 14:47.719
that I have loved you
for so long,

14:47.750 --> 14:51.948
and I've waited because
I thought it was too soon.

14:53.320 --> 14:55.152
- Now I told you too late.

14:58.390 --> 15:00.996
The witch that
I told you about,

15:01.030 --> 15:03.124
the one who
did this to me,

15:03.170 --> 15:05.867
when I die,
she gets my soul.

15:05.900 --> 15:08.790
And when I made that deal,
I thought I was OK with it.

15:08.840 --> 15:12.003
But now, I'm scared.

15:14.640 --> 15:16.438
- Where does it stop?

15:16.480 --> 15:19.541
What if this doesn't work?
What if you come for me?

15:19.580 --> 15:21.674
- I would never hurt you.

15:27.760 --> 15:32.084
- The reason that I helped you
in the first place...

15:33.060 --> 15:35.700
it's the same reason
that I can't help you now.

15:35.730 --> 15:39.724
Watching over the dead
is my responsibility.

15:39.770 --> 15:41.989
If you knew me at all,

15:42.040 --> 15:45.032
you'd know better
than to ask that.

15:54.420 --> 15:57.185
- Hey. Any word from Sally?

15:57.220 --> 16:00.758
- Yeah, she's, uh,
safe and sound.

16:00.790 --> 16:04.226
- Cool. Um, so you're
looking at magazines?

16:04.260 --> 16:05.523
Uh...

16:05.560 --> 16:07.096
- We're planning
our honeymoon.

16:07.130 --> 16:09.519
- Did you set a date already?
- Thursday.

16:09.560 --> 16:15.260
We wanted to make sure that
Sally was still... in town.

16:15.300 --> 16:16.529
